@startuml darknote Premium architecture
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

package "darknote (Next.js app)" {
  package "Baseline (pre-existing context)" {
    [Send / Read UI] as UI
    [lib/crypto.ts\n(NaCl box, key derivation)] as Crypto
    [lib/db.ts\n(notes, keys)] as DB
  }
  package "Premium Notes (assessed increment)" {
    [POST /api/notes\n(premium gate)] as Route
    [lib/premium.ts\n(classify + enforce)] as Premium
    [lib/x402.ts\n(terms + parse)] as X402
    [lib/premiumStore.ts\n(atomic nonce redeem)] as Store
    [GET /api/pricing\n(discovery)] as Pricing
  }
}

[Browser wallet] as Wallet <<external>>
[x402 facilitator] as Fac <<external>>
database "SQLite\n(darknote.db)" as SQLite

UI --> Crypto : encrypt in browser
UI --> Route : create note
Route --> Premium : classify + enforce tier
Route --> X402 : build 402 terms / parse payment
Route --> Fac : verify + settle (premium only)
Route --> Store : redeem nonce (atomic, once)
Route --> DB : create note (ciphertext only)
Store --> SQLite
DB --> SQLite
UI <--> Wallet : sign

note bottom of Premium
  Assessed work. The free path is untouched
  and never pays; only premium capability is
  gated. Server-side enforcement — a client
  cannot inflate limits (NFR2).
end note
@enduml
